Let's get you set up and ready to play! Don't worry if this is your first time
with an Atari 2600 - we'll walk you through every step.

@section What You Need

Before you start your fighting adventure, make sure you have:

@enumerate
@item
@strong{An Atari 2600 Console} - This is the main game system. It's a small
rectangular box with wood-grain trim (or black plastic on later models). On the
front, you'll see a power switch, some other switches, and a slot for game
cartridges. The back has connections for your TV and controllers.

@item
@strong{At least one Joystick Controller} - This is what you'll use to control
your fighter! It looks like a black stick on a square base, with a red button
on the side. You can play with just one joystick, but ChaosFight is way more
fun with friends, so grab as many as you can (up to four)!

@item
@strong{The ChaosFight Game Cartridge} - That's what you're holding! The game
is stored on this cartridge, which slides into the Atari 2600 console.

@item
@strong{A Television} - Any TV with a coaxial (screw-on) antenna connection will
work great! If you have a modern flat-screen TV, you might need a special adapter
box to connect the Atari 2600 (ask at your local electronics store for an
"RF modulator" if you need help).
@end enumerate

@section Let's Get Playing!

Follow these simple steps and you'll be fighting in no time:

@enumerate
@item
@strong{First, make sure everything is OFF!} Turn off your Atari 2600 (if it's
on) and your TV. Safety first!

@item
@strong{Connect your TV.} Attach the cable from your Atari 2600 to your TV's
antenna input. This usually screws on. If you're not sure which connection to
use, look for the one that says "ANT IN" or "RF IN" on your TV.

@item
@strong{Plug in the controllers.} On the back of the Atari 2600, you'll see
two controller ports (they look like rectangular openings). Plug your joystick(s)
into these ports:
@itemize @bullet
@item @strong{Player 1:} Use the @strong{LEFT} port (usually labeled "1")
@item @strong{Player 2:} Use the @strong{RIGHT} port (usually labeled "2")
@item @strong{Players 3 & 4:} If you have a special Quadtari adapter, see
@ref{Controller Configuration} for details on setting up four players!
@end itemize

@item
@strong{Insert the game cartridge.} Find the cartridge slot on top of the Atari
2600 (it's the wide opening). Gently but firmly slide the ChaosFight cartridge
into the slot until it's seated snugly. @emph{Remember: Always insert and remove
cartridges while the power is OFF!}

@item
@strong{Turn on your TV} and select channel 3 or channel 4. (Most Atari 2600s
use channel 3, but check the switch on the back of your console - it should say
"CH 3" or "CH 4".) You might need to use your TV's "Antenna" or "TV" input mode
rather than "Video" or "HDMI."

@item
@strong{Power up the Atari 2600!} Flip the power switch on the console. You
should see the TV screen change - that means it's working!

@item
@strong{Watch the intro!} ChaosFight will show you two special screens:
@itemize @bullet
@item The @strong{Publisher Screen} (AtariAge) with a cool jingle
@item The @strong{Author Screen} (Interworldly Adventuring) with theme music
@item The @strong{Title Screen} with fighters running past
@end itemize

You can press the @strong{red fire button} on any joystick to skip ahead, or
just sit back and enjoy the show!

@item
@strong{Start fighting!} Once you see the title screen, press the fire button
to begin choosing your characters. See @ref{Character Selection} to learn how
to pick your fighter!
@end enumerate

@strong{Troubleshooting Quick Tips:}

@itemize @bullet
@item
@strong{Black screen?} Make sure your TV is on the right channel (3 or 4) and
set to "Antenna" or "TV" mode.

@item
@strong{Snowy/fuzzy picture?} Try the other channel (3 or 4). Also check that
the cable is screwed on tightly.

@item
@strong{Joystick not working?} Make sure it's plugged in firmly and try pressing
the fire button at the title screen to "wake up" the controller detection.
@end itemize

@strong{Special Note for Multicart Users:}@footnote{Using a multicart device
like a Harmony, Uno, or flash cartridge? These awesome devices let you store
hundreds of games! After turning on your Atari 2600, you'll first see your
multicart's menu. Use your joystick to navigate to the ChaosFight ROM file and
press fire to load it. Check your multicart's instruction manual if you need
help navigating the menu!}

