Did you know you can use a Sega Genesis or Mega Drive controller with your
Atari 2600? These controllers have a more modern feel and work great with
ChaosFight!

@strong{What You Need:}

A standard 3-button Genesis/Mega Drive controller. These controllers use the
same 9-pin connector as Atari joysticks, so they plug right in! (Note: 6-button
Genesis controllers may not work reliably.)

@strong{How to Use It in ChaosFight:}

@table @strong
@item D-Pad (Directional Pad)
The cross-shaped button pad controls movement:
@itemize @bullet
@item @strong{LEFT/RIGHT:} Move and turn your fighter
@item @strong{UP:} Jump
@item @strong{DOWN:} Guard (block attacks)
@item @strong{Diagonals:} Press two directions at once for diagonal movement
@end itemize

@item Buttons A, B, or C
@strong{Any of these three buttons works as the Fire button!} Press whichever
one feels most comfortable to you - they all do the same thing in ChaosFight.
@itemize @bullet
@item Attack with your character's weapon
@item Lock in character selection
@item Confirm menu choices
@end itemize

@item START Button
The START button isn't used in ChaosFight (we use the console's Game Select
switch instead for pausing).
@end table

@strong{Why Use a Genesis Controller?}

@itemize @bullet
@item @strong{More comfortable:} The ergonomic design fits nicely in your hands
@item @strong{Precise D-pad:} Some players find it easier to hit exact directions
@item @strong{Three buttons:} Even though ChaosFight only needs one button, having
three means you can press whichever one is easiest!
@item @strong{Great for long play sessions:} Less hand fatigue than the CX-40 stick
@end itemize

@strong{Important Note:}

Genesis controllers and Quadtari adapters @strong{don't work together}. If
ChaosFight detects a Genesis controller, it will automatically disable Quadtari
mode. For 4-player games, stick with standard CX-40 joysticks and a Quadtari!

