Are you a ChaosFight master looking for an extra challenge? Or maybe you want
to even the odds when playing against less experienced friends? ChaosFight
includes a built-in handicapping system!

@strong{How to Activate Handicap Mode:}

@enumerate
@item
Browse to your chosen character normally using LEFT/RIGHT on the joystick.

@item
@strong{Hold DOWN on the joystick} before pressing the fire button.

@item
While holding DOWN, @strong{press and hold the FIRE BUTTON} to lock in your
selection.

@item
Your character preview will @strong{freeze in a "recovery" pose} - this is your
visual confirmation that handicap mode is active! The character will no longer
animate, staying in their "recovering from far fall" stance.

@item
Your status bar will still fill with your player colour, showing you're locked
in.
@end enumerate

@strong{What Handicap Mode Does:}

When you activate handicap mode during character selection:

@itemize @bullet
@item
Your starting health is @strong{reduced to 75 points} (instead of the normal 100)

@item
This is a @strong{25% health reduction} - a significant disadvantage!

@item
All other game mechanics remain the same (movement, attacks, damage, etc.)

@item
There's no visual indicator during gameplay, but your health bar will start
shorter than other players
@end itemize

@strong{Why Use Handicap Mode?}

@itemize @bullet
@item
@strong{Challenge yourself!} Test your skills with less margin for error

@item
@strong{Balance skill gaps:} Let experienced players handicap themselves when
playing with beginners

@item
@strong{Create tournaments:} Use handicaps to make competitions more interesting

@item
@strong{Learn characters:} Practise with handicaps to really master your fighter's
abilities

@item
@strong{Show off:} Beat your friends with one hand tied behind your back (well,
25% less health!)
@end itemize

@strong{Tips for Handicap Play:}

@itemize @bullet
@item
Choose heavy characters like Ursulo or Knight Guy - they can take fewer hits,
so their extra weight helps

@item
Perfect your guard timing - you can't afford to take unnecessary damage!

@item
Play defensively - let your opponents make mistakes

@item
Use ranged characters to keep distance and avoid risky close combat

@item
Learn the arenas well - use platforms and obstacles to your advantage
@end itemize

@strong{Visual Confirmation:}

The frozen "recovery pose" during character selection is your guarantee that
handicap mode is active. If the character is still animating normally, you
didn't activate it - try again, making sure to hold DOWN @emph{before} pressing
fire!

